<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="520" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/418: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-15T16:00:00-04:00">September 15, 1930—4
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>322. Your 813, September 15, noon. Authorization granted. Has
                            presentation of draft by the British Minister received any
                            publicity?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>